{"batch":"Abstractions & Dependencies","batch_index":2,"assessments":{"abstraction_fitness":72.4},"dimension_notes":{"abstraction_fitness":{"evidence":["Large callback-bag runtimes are used as pseudo-DI containers across modules (for example `importerRuntime` in `goseg/importer/importer.go` and `workflowRuntime` in `goseg/shipworkflow/operations_runtime.go`), with many function fields that must be validated and merged before use.","Service registration in startup orchestration is represented in multiple parallel structures (`startBackgroundServiceSpecs`, `serviceCallbacks()` map, and `setServiceCallback` switch in `goseg/startuporchestrator/startup_orchestrator.go`), increasing abstraction maintenance cost and drift risk.","Runtime resolution/validation is repeatedly performed deep in helper paths (for example `resolveImporterRuntimeForWorkflow` and `resolveWorkflowRuntime` calls inside operational helpers), which adds indirection cost and obscures true dependency boundaries.","Global singleton event runtime is mixed with injectable runtime patterns (`events.DefaultEventRuntime()` in `goseg/docker/events/events.go`, used directly in `goseg/importer/importer.go` and captured in `goseg/shipworkflow/operations_runtime.go`), creating inconsistent abstraction ownership."],"impact_scope":"subsystem","fix_scope":"architectural_change","confidence":"high","sub_axes":{"abstraction_leverage":66.0,"indirection_cost":58.5,"interface_honesty":71.0}}},"findings":[{"dimension":"abstraction_fitness","identifier":"callback_bag_runtime_sprawl","summary":"Wide callback-bag runtimes create low-leverage indirection across orchestration paths","related_files":["goseg/importer/importer.go","goseg/shipworkflow/operations_runtime.go","goseg/docker/orchestration/runtime_ops.go","goseg/startuporchestrator/startup_orchestrator.go"],"evidence":["`importerRuntime` embeds three runtime structs with many callbacks and requires multiple requirement-specific validators (`validateImporter*Runtime`).","`workflowRuntime` embeds multiple orchestration op structs plus custom callbacks, then repeatedly resolves through `seams.ResolveRuntime`.","`runtime_ops.go` defines many granular `*Ops` structs that mainly forward existing package functions, then assembles them into a registry bundle.","`startup_orchestrator.go` defines multiple runtime structs for init/background/runtime phases with callback fields and group-tag validation."],"suggestion":"Collapse function-bag structs into a smaller set of capability interfaces per workflow (for example `ImportProvisioner`, `TransitionPublisher`, `ContainerController`) and inject concrete services once at orchestration boundaries instead of passing merged callback structs through inner helpers.","confidence":"high","impact_scope":"subsystem","fix_scope":"architectural_change","root_cause_cluster":"runtime_indirection_overuse"},{"dimension":"abstraction_fitness","identifier":"startup_service_registry_triplication","summary":"Background-service abstraction is triplicated across spec list, callback map, and setter switch","related_files":["goseg/startuporchestrator/startup_orchestrator.go","goseg/startuporchestrator/startup_orchestrator_test.go"],"evidence":["Service identity is maintained in `startBackgroundServiceName` constants and again in `startBackgroundServiceSpecs`.","`serviceCallbacks()` separately maps each constant to runtime fields.","`setServiceCallback()` repeats the same mapping as a long `switch`, requiring synchronized edits for every new service and creating drift-prone abstraction bookkeeping."],"suggestion":"Introduce a single canonical service descriptor table containing name, fail-fast policy, WG requirement, and getter/setter adapters for callback fields; generate specs and callback binding from that table to remove manual triplication.","confidence":"high","impact_scope":"module","fix_scope":"multi_file_refactor","root_cause_cluster":"runtime_indirection_overuse"},{"dimension":"abstraction_fitness","identifier":"runtime_resolution_in_inner_paths","summary":"Runtime resolution is repeated inside inner helpers instead of once per request/workflow","related_files":["goseg/importer/importer.go","goseg/shipworkflow/operations_runtime.go","goseg/main.go"],"evidence":["Importer helpers (`finalizeUploadOnCompletion`, `configureUploadedPier`, `runImportedPierWorkflow`, `allChunksReceived`) each resolve runtime independently via variadic runtime parameters.","Workflow helpers (`publishTransition`, `emitWorkflowTransition`, `persistShipConf`, `urbitCleanDelete`, `areSubdomainsAliases`) repeatedly call `resolveWorkflowRuntime` in local helper scope.","`main.go` follows the same pattern with runtime wrappers (`bootstrapRuntimeWith`, `runBootstrapSubsystems`) that re-resolve/validate callback carriers rather than operating on a fully-resolved dependency object through the call chain."],"suggestion":"Resolve runtime/dependencies once at entrypoints (HTTP handler, startup task, workflow dispatcher) and pass a concrete resolved dependency object through downstream calls; remove variadic runtime parameters from inner helpers to make dependency contracts explicit.","confidence":"high","impact_scope":"subsystem","fix_scope":"multi_file_refactor","root_cause_cluster":"runtime_indirection_overuse"},{"dimension":"abstraction_fitness","identifier":"event_runtime_ownership_split","summary":"Event publishing abstraction mixes global singleton and injected broker semantics","related_files":["goseg/docker/events/events.go","goseg/shipworkflow/operations_runtime.go","goseg/importer/importer.go"],"evidence":["`events` package exposes mutable process-wide default runtime (`DefaultEventRuntime`, `SetDefaultEventRuntime`).","`workflowRuntime` carries an `EventRuntime` field but transition publishing actually goes through a separate `TransitionEmitter` closure captured from `DefaultEventRuntime()` at construction time.","Importer default runtime binds `PublishImportTransitionFn` directly to `events.DefaultEventRuntime().PublishImportShipTransition`, bypassing explicit broker ownership per operation context."],"suggestion":"Pick one ownership model for event publishing: either fully injected broker per runtime (preferred) or centralized singleton. If injected, derive `TransitionEmitter` from the injected broker and remove direct `DefaultEventRuntime()` usage from runtime constructors.","confidence":"medium","impact_scope":"subsystem","fix_scope":"architectural_change","root_cause_cluster":"runtime_indirection_overuse"}],"retrospective":{"root_causes":["Testability-by-callback strategy expanded into production architecture, creating broad function-bag runtimes.","Lack of canonical service/dependency descriptors leads to parallel registries and repeated glue code.","Mixed global-singleton and dependency-injection approaches blur ownership boundaries."],"likely_symptoms":["startup_service_registry_triplication","runtime_resolution_in_inner_paths","event_runtime_ownership_split"],"possible_false_positives":[]}}


